feed.title: Wybejong Park Riddells Creek Flora And Fauna

entry.title: Suta flagellum
entry.content: Found under tin at Wybejong Park working bee. Record and photo by Lyn Hovey. First record of this species in Riddells Creek.

entry.content: Mating.

entry.title: Sceliphron laetum
entry.content: The size of this wasp took me by surprise when it flew by - a very large wasp.

entry.title: Vanessa kershawi
entry.content: In what I think is Mentha X piperita (weed).

entry.title: Austroagrion watsoni
entry.content: Male.

entry.title: Ornduffia reniformis
entry.content: Also a male Austroagrion watsoni sitting on a leaf in pic2.

entry.title: Austrolestes leda
entry.content: Male 'guarding' female as she lays eggs on Triglochin procera s.l.. New species record for Riddells Creek (no. 21). 11th species recorded at Wybejong.

entry.title: Phalaenoides glycinae
entry.content: Feeding in planted Westringia.

entry.title: Ischnura aurora
entry.content: Tiny damselfly. New species record for Riddells Creek.

entry.title: Cordulephya pygmaea
entry.content: Autumn flying dragonfly. Rests with wings held shut.

entry.title: Mentha X piperita, Pieris rapae rapae
entry.content: Leaves petiolate and 9cm x 3cm further down the stem.

entry.title: Myriophyllum crispatum
entry.content: Leaves terete in upper 90% of plant with a few lobed leaves at base. Leaves 6-whorled. Buds fusiform.

entry.title: Hemicordulia australiae
entry.content: Mating pair. New species record for Riddells Creek.

entry.title: Acrida conica
entry.content: Very large grasshopper. Seen heaps this year for the first time on the grassland rail reserves but never been able to get close to one (very flighty).

entry.title: Ischnura heterosticta heterosticta
entry.content: Two spots on back of the head is a distinguishing feature for this species.

entry.title: Diplacodes bipunctata
entry.content: Flying in a dried up, rocky creek bed along with male D. haematodes and male O. caledonicum among other species.

entry.title: Ocybadistes walkeri sothis
entry.content: Different individuals in the two pics.

entry.title: Cordulephya pygmaea
entry.content: Tiny dragonfly (a true dragonfly with the wings held together - like a damselfly). A new species record for Riddells Creek.

entry.title: Orthetrum caledonicum
entry.content: I saw this dragonfly tucking into what looks like a fly or bee (looks a bit like a Cuckoo Bee). No females observed.

entry.title: Diplacodes haematodes
entry.content: New species record for Riddells Creek. 2nd & 3rd pic shows yellowish colouring on proximal half of wing - an ID feature for this species. No females seen.

entry.title: Elatine gratioloides
entry.content: Seems to be a new species record for the Macedon Range. On the northern creekside at Wybejong Park.

entry.title: Persicaria decipiens, Zizina labradus labradus
entry.content: Lots flying around the Persicaria on the creekside.

entry.title: Heteronympha penelope penelope
entry.content: I think landed on some old Yorkshire Fog.

entry.title: Geitoneura acantha
entry.content: Females, like this one, are much larger compared to males.
